50|$|Hydraulic or {{electric}} actuators add controlled {{energy to the}} steering mechanism, so the driver can provide less effort to turn the <b>steered</b> <b>wheels</b> when driving at typical speeds, and reduce considerably the physical effort necessary to turn the wheels when a vehicle is stopped or moving slowly. Power steering can also be engineered to provide some artificial feedback of forces acting on the <b>steered</b> <b>wheels.</b>|$|E
